#!/usr/bin/perl
use strict;
use warnings;
use Getopt::Long;
use Pod::Usage;

=encoding utf8

=head1 NAME

fairy - Generate distribution packages, as if by magic!

=head1 SYNOPSIS

fairy [options] <package>

=head1 DESCRIPTION

Fairy attempts to generate a distribution package from the given source
repository using the given template.  The package will be generated in
the current working directory.

=head1 OPTIONS

=over 4

=item B<--source|-s SOURCE>

The source repository of the package.  Could be either I<file>, I<cpan>
or I<github>.  Defaults to I<file>, if present, or I<cpan> otherwise.

=item B<--template|-t TEMPLATE>

The template to use for package generation.  A handful of templates
is installed by default, others can be placed in the I<templates>
directory.  See the FILES section.  Defaults to I<fedora-perl>.

=item B<--lang|-l LANGUAGE>

Some sources know what language the package is written in while some
others are more generic (e.g. I<file> or I<github>) and will need your
advice.  Defaults to I<perl>.

=item B<--hints|-h HINTSFILE>

Ammend the generated metadata.  See the HINTS FILES section for details.

=back

=head1 HINTS FILES

...

=head1 EXAMPLES

    fairy App-Fairy-0.42.tar.gz
    fairy --source cpan --template fedora-perl App::Fairy
    fairy --source github --template fedora-perl --lang perl contyk/fairy

=head1 FILES

=over 4

=item B<~/.fairy/templates>

Directory with custom L<Template::Toolkit> template files.

=back

=head1 AUTHOR AND LICENSE

Copyright © 2015 Petr Šabata <contyk@redhat.com>

See the LICENSE file for licensing details.

=cut

pod2usage(-message => "Sorry, the magic is not implemented yet!\n",
    -sections => 'SYNOPSIS|OPTIONS|EXAMPLES',
    -verbose => 99,
    -exitval => 1);
